# M6 P07 — pre-round countdown visibility test.
#
# The new flow: when the lobby auto-start fires, start_round prepares
# the world (mech spawn, mode = MODE_MATCH) AND enters
# MATCH_PHASE_COUNTDOWN. Players see the rendered world plus a big
# "1" / "GO!" number in the screen center; inputs are locked.
#
# Burst captures cover the LOBBY → COUNTDOWN → ACTIVE transitions.
# In shot mode the countdown is forced to 1 s (60 ticks) for
# iteration speed, so the COUNTDOWN frames sit roughly ticks 120-180
# (after a 1 s lobby auto-start + the 60-tick countdown). Look for:
#   * a large "1" centered on screen during COUNTDOWN frames
#   * a brief "GO!" right at the COUNTDOWN→ACTIVE seam
#   * the world rendered behind the countdown number, with the
#     player's mech at its spawn (not moving — input is locked)

window 1280 720
seed 1 0
out build/shots/m6_countdown
network host 24700
name HostA
loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Sidearm" Light Standard
map slipstream
no_parallax

# Capture the lobby → countdown → active arc.
burst t from 100 to 260 every 10

at 320 end

contact_sheet sheet cols 6 cell 320 180
